<subSubSection id="3854823249546E95DC4EE331659D7B5D" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph id="D50AC71BA87D166F92A90C5D7E2485E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A25A418DAD86E13EBF3637C4A9B0047" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Frustule shape is cylindrical to approximately octagonal (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="145707ACCA7EC345741B3D03A3175D2D" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM (A-D, H) and LM (E-G) images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city: A-G Melosira subglobosa (A, F girdle views, B-E, G, valve views) H Melosira varians, partial valve view and girdle view of complete frustule. Scale bars: 10 μm (A-C, E-H); 20 μm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545734" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">2A, F</figureCitation>
). Valve 12.5-26 
<normalizedToken id="04E0622740B5BCDFCADB3686B5C1B6EF" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter, mantle height 3.1-8.5 
<normalizedToken id="66E295EE442C24F028377B262C367C6D" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Valve face nearly octagonal with flat tops (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9B5C63E639774C5786DC639D98242CB5" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM (A-D, H) and LM (E-G) images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city: A-G Melosira subglobosa (A, F girdle views, B-E, G, valve views) H Melosira varians, partial valve view and girdle view of complete frustule. Scale bars: 10 μm (A-C, E-H); 20 μm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545734" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">2B-E, G</figureCitation>
). Girdle with puncta forming straight and transverse rows 32-56 in 10 
<normalizedToken id="758F64AF0673DF76EFF78B07396EA994" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="4F63846BCA5AB72997EF668B4253EA20" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545734" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="891C97C96C553E0A5D0694EE41100B29" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="E9C6EA2FE15F26E1BE965B38CD827D6C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Figure 2.</emphasis>
SEM (
<emphasis id="17629BAFF41EC5E532653597D8857CBA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A-D, H</emphasis>
) and LM (
<emphasis id="BE8A6D33B9B1D5E53BB942CB8DFCF9DC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">E-G</emphasis>
) images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city: 
<emphasis id="BA9E88CB3D4D9DE4F0806CC0850D4313" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A-G</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="64884891432143D8AE26FF16A56EFE05" authority="" authorityName="" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Melosiraceae" genus="Melosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melosira subglobosa" order="Melosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="subglobosa">
<emphasis id="5A80F868DD988570E1A7611F2300A7DB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Melosira subglobosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="CD4667CC89B7616B5333E8132095E46E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A, F</emphasis>
girdle views, 
<emphasis id="72B983BE256EF4060AC53FCFFCB19126" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">B-E, G</emphasis>
, valve views) 
<emphasis id="1E799C6ABBC690712D00BF146EB6AF7F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">H</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B1CCBFA34E6CAADD14C8DA16C6492F5A" authority="" authorityName="" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Melosiraceae" genus="Melosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melosira varians" order="Melosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="varians">
