</taxonomicName>
, partial valve view and girdle view of complete frustule. Scale bars: 10 
<normalizedToken id="2409305F2C031CB6E322C3AE2EB3C235" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="01E2A78A75762807A27C28F8FBDD6432" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A-C, E-H</emphasis>
); 20 
<normalizedToken id="153BB58EBFBB793C5C2B65C4A6F1FF62" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="F37A01A6D8136A9550844A03C3D76CE9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91D8EEA8B70C7224DE1CEE613DF6462C" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="62B9C0D83CDE3FFA61A091E27EA15BED" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F70F19AA7A0AF1B4B482E22EA8F61926" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Marine and brackish, benthic-planktonic (tychoplanktonic) species, halophilic, widely distributed. Indicates significant organic pollution (eutrophication), 
<normalizedToken id="A89AEED527BCF58DF9F50DED2D03E172" originalValue="α-mesosaprobiont">α-mesosaprobiont</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F52E279AED4D4A4A0EF5F0CEE6640A3B" author="Kolpacov, NV" journalOrPublisher="Izvestiya TINRO" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="127 - 138" refId="B72" refString="Kolpacov, NV, Begun, AA, Olkhovick, AV, 2014. Sostav I raspredelenie mikrovodoroslej v estuarii reki Sukhodol (Ussuriysky zaliv, zaliv Petra Velikhogo) v osennij period. 2. Epipithon. Izvestiya TINRO 176: 127 - 138" title="Sostav I raspredelenie mikrovodoroslej v estuarii reki Sukhodol (Ussuriysky zaliv, zaliv Petra Velikhogo) v osennij period. 2. Epipithon." volume="176" year="2014">Kolpacov et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). This species prefers water enriched with dissolved organic matter, and is capable to switch from autotrophic to heterotrophic or mixed type of nutrition (
<bibRefCitation id="0696D045DE1A5BB6A96819AF73DBF656" author="Andreeva, NA" journalOrPublisher="BMC Evolutionary Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B4" refString="Andreeva, NA, Smornova, LL, Antonova, LS, 2008. Algoflora morskikh donnykh otlozheniy, zagryaznennykh khimicheskimi toksikantami (Kerchensky proliv, Chernoe more). Sovremennye problemy algologii: mat. Mezhdunar. nauch. konf. i VII Shkoly po morskoy biol. Rostov n/D, 14-16." title="Algoflora morskikh donnykh otlozheniy, zagryaznennykh khimicheskimi toksikantami (Kerchensky proliv, Chernoe more). Sovremennye problemy algologii: mat. Mezhdunar. nauch. konf. i VII Shkoly po morskoy biol. Rostov n / D, 14 - 16." year="2008">Andreeva et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, these diatoms are ubiquitous, and widely distributed in seas and estuaries of temperate zones in habitats with a moderate level with increased level of human impact (
<bibRefCitation id="38457693452DF59BA0E631982BA630BA" author="Kuzminova, NS" journalOrPublisher="Algologiya" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="128 - 141" refId="B80" refString="Kuzminova, NS, Rudneva, II, 2005. Vliyanie stochnykh vod na morskie vodorosli. Algologiya 15 (1): 128 - 141" title="Vliyanie stochnykh vod na morskie vodorosli." volume="15" year="2005">Kuzminova and Rudneva 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7AD76E17E74FE0B11DB7C55F1F0CBA52" author="Ryabushko, LI" journalOrPublisher="Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B106" refString="Ryabushko, LI, 2009. Mikrofithobenthos Chernogo morya: autoref. dis.. ... dr. biol. nauk. Sevaltopol, 48 pp." title="Mikrofithobenthos Chernogo morya: autoref. dis .. ... dr. biol. nauk. Sevaltopol, 48 pp." year="2009">Ryabushko 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="95FB75E5F68F79C985FACFBE4729CB13" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1103C69E068FF2985802511310C001F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="487E586560B359BE22ABA1848AEAC98B" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="BEF3232DB6B5711C80A777A3BB2E44A4" authority="" authorityName="" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Melosiraceae" genus="Melosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melosira subglobosa" order="Melosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="subglobosa">
<emphasis id="273206F8CD3D8EA1F3F72B374CDC7684" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Melosira subglobosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the most common species at the sampling sites near the Mykolaiv area in the Southern Bug River (Table 
<tableCitation id="714CF732A5C4D1091DA5769F605BA496" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
). For Ukrainian territory, it is known from the coastal zone in the northwestern part of the Black Sea, Crimean seaboard, and some estuaries.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9E0D4F0B4940FB46026751203F68556" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
For a worldwide distribution, it was recorded from coastal zones of Europe, and Asia; specifically, from Lake Aral, Baltic, Bering, Black, Caspian, Mediterranean, North and Norway Seas (
<bibRefCitation id="B18756FADFA19E26EB3D3A27404CD48B" author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
